John,<br>
Good (hard) questions! I truely don't know if I believe anything that Clinton or the Gov't says. I have been lied to so many times by so many different presidents and officials that I don't thin I would ever trust any of them. It would help if there was more international support for our actions from those who are a part of the developing world. When we did the Gulf war we had support of many Arab nations, as well as much of the UN in general. <br><br>
I can't help but think that the Exxons, Gulf, Mobil, Shell and other oil companies are the ones who benefit from our actions. How do you or I benefit?<br><br>
I think that as a nation we would feel awful if Israel got attacked. I hope (but doubt) that we would also feel awful if we have to attack and kill Iraqi's. Is there no other path we could have taken prior to the Gulf war? Is there o other path other than the one we are looking at now?<br><br>
By the way, If Bill Clinton was an anti-war protester then I am Ho Chi Min! He may have been to a demonstration or even two, but it has always looked to me like the actions of a dillatant. &quot;Oh boy, this was fun... lets go and smoke some dope now without inhaling&quot; .
